    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Mondragone marble is a slightly metamorphosed yellow or gray carbonate rock, which was widely employed as monumental stone in the 18th-century royal palaces of Naples and Caserta. Named for Mondragone, Campania where the marble is quarried.</Note_Text>
